On September 19, 2019, President Donald Trump issued a statement declaring the continuation of the national emergency with respect to persons who commit, threaten to commit, or support terrorism. This national emergency was initially declared on September 23, 2001, in response to the terrorist attacks on September 11, 2001. The President stated that the actions of individuals involved in terrorism still pose an extraordinary threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. The continuation of this national emergency is in accordance with the National Emergencies Act. The notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.